# === Multipart / file upload specs ===
# type/file: Convenience methods reference File model types via refkeys, but
# these file models don't have JSON/XML usage and are filtered from generation.
# File download operations need special handling to return BinaryData/stream
# instead of model types in convenience methods.
type/file

# === Multi-namespace scope issues — FIXED ===
# Fixed by adding rootNamespace using to cross-namespace client files
# and only setting flavor=azure for azure/* directory paths in emit-e2e.ts.

# === service/multi-service — separate bug ===
# CombinedOptions class is missing Version property; Generated constructor
# references options.Version but ClientOptionsFile does not generate it.
service/multi-service

# === Overload / Naming — Azure API surface in non-Azure specs ===
# client/overload: Generated convenience methods use Azure.Core types
# (DiagnosticScope, Response.GetRawResponse) in non-Azure context. Also has
# CS0136 scope variable redeclaration in nested try blocks.
# client/naming: UnionEnum convenience methods pass BinaryContent where
# extensible enum type is expected; also uses Azure.RequestContext in non-Azure
# context (overload resolution picks wrong protocol method).
client/overload
client/naming
